tmjos-shell-tweaks (1.3.0-3) noble; urgency=medium

  * Replace failed CSS hack with a 4-line GJS extension.
  * 1.3.0-1's approach (dpkg-divert on Yaru CSS) didn't actually
    hide the button on GNOME 46 — panel selectors changed. The
    extension calls Main.panel.statusArea.activities.hide() instead,
    which works regardless of theme.
  * Extension installed at /usr/share/gnome-shell/extensions/
    tmjos-tweaks@tmjos.local/, enabled by tmjos-defaults's dconf
    override.
  * postinst migrates from 1.3.0-1: undoes the dpkg-divert on Yaru
    files so the upstream theme contents return.
  * Note on safety: GJS extensions are sandboxed by gnome-shell
    (no network, no exec, no filesystem outside GNOME APIs). The
    full source is in /usr/share/gnome-shell/extensions/
    tmjos-tweaks@tmjos.local/extension.js — auditable in 30 seconds.

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Sun, 10 May 2026 21:30:00 -0300

tmjos-shell-tweaks (1.3.0-1) noble; urgency=low

  * Initial .deb release.
  * Replaces phase 6e.2 of v1.2 customize.sh (CSS hack inline).
  * Uses dpkg-divert pra modificar Yaru theme files de forma reversível
    (original mantido como .tmjos-orig).
  * (Broken — CSS selector doesn't match GNOME 46 panel. Replaced
    in 1.3.0-3 with GJS extension + cleanup migration.)

